 just checks the builder count from AutoTimer.apply, which might not be significant. I should consider whether a new feature for percentile histogram publishing should be tested. It seems like there’s room to explore how these settings actually affect the Timer functionality! Let’s dig into this further.\\n\\n**Considering repository implementation**\\n\\nI need to ensure that the constructor result isn't null, but I shouldn't use an assertion for that. Instead, I might consider using RepositoryMethodInvocation, setting the repositoryInterface to SampleRepository.class. It's okay if there's no reflection metadata, as I can work with the class object. I'll also use method as null and focus on the result. Lastly, it might be useful to test for success and prepare for any exceptions that could come up.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0eac6986c1df3deb016a0cda6b47f88197b209e0d7303ff330\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqDNqG6NBizWrSaWYHfFBH-qg-etCRNqeoh6lj2aCfIfPvRR8bnTmxFGy7r4QDUit_jL9WU2A30qNCfUlkSiLktHrRiWcH4W8W4kDNxVpXcX3bqs_VUQdLAzsXaCK3vTvnbL2_oUQwYPfYOBEn5YQnwEn9dEG-BYOPtC6UNtyRJo7RrV6QaMXU_EZiwK-bg_hIaKZ_Mxt0I1DArp_KGhIeyeJEgGGr42iXOhjEnhVx5FSIqCH9bt0N_VBIs-HaSoNLt4OOzGrA62d5iUFNklQDGVfoAlnnKJMlDtAYWFuZmYOfJXJrhZrBul_F6utaQJbn6XZGE2_NqHomUi_HDGFaGJ3YolgfwWR-iUwIQ3M13BeaGAMJYarV6eqKn0ZEQuYD9gLJs3z4kvPHmcEYH-4cm5onkqv_nbqaxd9bwbL-3qZ-UpdaYWX6MWJUvz4gw-kImRbo6APrF5vGLDcdB0ARRTZYcWhgeYpFj-_IwxA9O5U9wVJ8uc5iiUjyZqSM3LAsYhtbS-9_oCs0qC4YlNi31CO9UFvREpu4R8FFQ-qM68AF3LO9kvzAwEhMoD36ddUn8ibmWFhrgqmlvTp_INsi0DHXqMh3kLPn7VMdoVqD03EtQmVRm-mRT6-vvsp5-rpO2Udzu1Q30X046-o4XN1H9GggGxJsB_O_Pql8Di54YCY4mS2DhaUWmYVEmJ6TXq4mtteycnEh4eG2iQmNd1W-h6Er5r_Ws6Oe8_TgxMDJ7_O2OdaLcGZzTguPitEAHayT1HaNTItUfcjBROwdritZoqySpqIFNNXrwzt9fg-kL0Q0lT6FEo5SFf39Lf2-7EzQopNDjpiOFUQNv0hRxhNyGCykoSX2Hz1ib-ungOzKje1UZwyi1ZrBZLQ1pmmHvOVdcNrcHkfgGjyrZcoCPmEjh8Ju4wpfFcq9rsIn_hYk0h-FVkhvuO1cLXBvkGxaeDCpwYtTb9gZdC3C3MwlGuNIK6pG-yK0jN_A7M_-ok3oV6v7qHx00sL-fcTceO