t a potential feature: DataWebAutoConfiguration customizers. So, existing tests only bind properties but don’t handle auto-configuration or customizers. But if I want to use a public API? The DataWebAutoConfiguration constructor is package-private, so I can’t access it outside the package.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test strategies**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about a testing strategy focusing on integration versus checking for duplicates in success flow. The user asked about testing new features, and I realize the existing listener success is mostly covered, but it doesn’t incorporate the @Timed annotation. Maybe having two tests is excessive. I wonder if I could consolidate and just keep one functional test for the TimedAnnotations instead of retesting already established logic flows. Adding a new direct test for TimedAnnotations seems more efficient.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing test coverage**\\\\n\\\\nI need to analyze the current coverage and consider writing tests for the new functional feature involving the @Timed annotation. My concern is about the extraTags array in the assertion and how class-level annotations interact with method annotations. It might be beneficial to name the test something like `timedAnnotationsPreferRepositoryMethodAnnotationsAndFallBackToTypeAnnotations` to cover method precedence and fallback in one go, without duplicates. I also need to ensure I've imported the right classes and handle the assertions correctly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_BbKXs7TMl8NpJ6LVDhqhNePe|fc_0f31f5ceec0fa013016a0cdb6000348197a21248f1f50b5a94\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-data-commons/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_data_commons/Spring_boot_data_commonsTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\", \"newText\": \"import java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\"}, {\"oldText\": \"import io.micrometer.core.instrument.Tag;\", \"newText\": \"import io.micrometer.core.annotation.Timed;\\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.Tag;\"}, {\"oldText\": \"import org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener;\", \"newText\": \"import org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener;\\nimport org.springframework.boot.data.metrics.TimedAnnotations;\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    void metricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListenerRecordsSuccessfulInvocations() {\\n        String metricName = \\\"test.repository.invocations\\\";\\n        long duration = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos(25);\\n        SimpleMeterRegistry registry = new SimpleMeterRegistry();\\n        MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener listener = new MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener(\\n                () -> registry, new DefaultRepositoryTagsProvider(), metricName, AutoTimer.ENABLED);\\n\\n        listener.afterInvocation(repositoryInvocation(State.SUCCESS, null, duration));\\n\\n        Timer timer = registry.get(metricName)\\n            .tags(\\\"repository\\\", \\\"SampleRepository\\\", \\\"state\\\", \\\"SUCCESS\\\", \\\"exception\\\", \\\"None\\\")\\n            .timer();\\n        assertThat(timer.count()).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(timer.totalTime(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)).isEqualTo(25.0);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static <T> T bind(String prefix, Class<T> type, Map<String, String> values) {\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    void metricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListenerRecordsSuccessfulInvocations() {\\n        String metricName = \\\"test.repository.invocations\\\";\\n        long duration = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos(25);\\n        SimpleMeterRegistry registry = new SimpleMeterRegistry();\\n        MetricsRepositoryMethodInvocationListener listener = new MetricsRepositoryMethodInv